Upon a summer’s morn,  
    With shadows long and still,  
    I walk where flowers were born,  
    Down by the gentle rill.

Each breath, a soft caress,  
    In harmony with time;  
    Nature’s sweet caress,  
    In rhythm and in rhyme.

- Edna St Vincent Millay
